# {{PROJECT_NAME}} CrewAI Engineering Planner

This directory contains a CrewAI scaffold that turns an engineering task description
into a reviewed, executable implementation plan. It pairs with
`.claude/scripts/engineering-loop.sh` to drive autonomous Claude Code sessions.

## Goals

- Take a single task description and produce an atomic, testable implementation plan.
- Have a second agent review the plan and tighten any ambiguity before execution.
- Output plain markdown that can be handed directly to Claude Code (or any IDE).

## Project Layout

- `src/{{PY_PACKAGE}}/crew.py` - CrewAI agents, tasks, and orchestration.
- `src/{{PY_PACKAGE}}/config/agents.yaml` - Agent role, goal, and backstory config.
- `src/{{PY_PACKAGE}}/config/tasks.yaml` - Task prompts and expected outputs.
- `src/{{PY_PACKAGE}}/main.py` - CLI entrypoint (`--task`, `--context-files`).

## Setup

```bash
cd .crewai
cp .env.example .env
# choose direct API mode or proxy mode in .env
uv sync
```

### Optional: CLIProxyAPI (Subscription-Backed Routing)

```bash
# from repo root
bash .claude/scripts/crewai-cliproxyapi.sh up
```

Then configure providers/subscription clients in CLIProxyAPI and run CrewAI with
`CREWAI_LLM_MODE=proxy` in `.crewai/.env`.
Set `ENGINEERING_MODEL` to a model or alias exposed by your proxy config
(default scaffold value: `gpt-5.3-codex`).

## Run

Plan a single engineering task and print the result to stdout:

```bash
cd .crewai
uv run python -m {{PY_PACKAGE}}.main --task "Add JWT auth to the API"
```

Pass extra context files (comma-separated):

```bash
uv run python -m {{PY_PACKAGE}}.main \
  --task "Add JWT auth to the API" \
  --context-files "../README.md,../src/api.py"
```

Dry run (no LLM call — just echoes the assembled inputs):

```bash
uv run python -m {{PY_PACKAGE}}.main --task "Add JWT auth to the API" --dry-run
```

## Optional: Write the Plan to a File

Set `ENGINEERING_PLAN_OUTPUT` to an absolute path, or
`ENGINEERING_PLAN_BASE_DIR` to a base directory (a `<task-slug>/PRD.md` file
is written under it). The host driver `.claude/scripts/engineering-loop.sh`
sets these automatically when `--use-planner` is enabled.
